description: Unique identifier for this labor line record.
System timestamp when this record was created or last updated (to the millisecond).
Flag indicating the labor entry is manager-controlled (e.g., scheduled/allocated by a supervisor) rather than ad‑hoc; confirm with SME.
Short description of the task or service performed.
Technician or service notes for this labor entry.
Row version counter used for concurrency or change tracking.
Extended labor amount charged for this line (rate multiplied by quantity), in currency.
Total hours accounted for on this labor line, in decimal hours.
Quantity allocated by management for this labor (typically hours). Used to compare scheduled vs actual; confirm with SME.
Units applied to this labor line (typically hours) used to calculate charges.
Billing rate applied to this labor, typically per hour.
Code indicating the tax category applied to the labor charge.
Reference source that defines the labor tax category code; confirm with SME.
Identifier of the labor resource who performed the work (e.g., technician/employee/vendor).
Type of labor resource referenced by the identifier (e.g., employee, contractor).
Internal identifier of the associated work order this labor is posted against.
Reference source for the associated work order identifier (table/type indicator).
Work order number linked to this labor entry (display or external identifier).
Reference source for the work order number (table/type indicator).
Identifier from a prior system for migration or cross‑reference.
Name of the source table in a prior system for migration mapping.
Human‑readable rendering of the recorded time (e.g., HH:MM).
Minutes captured via time clock for this labor entry.
Hours captured via time clock for this labor entry.
Planned end time of the labor activity (time of day).
Planned start time of the labor activity (time of day).
Indicates whether the technician is currently clocked into this task.
Flag to prevent automatic updates from the originating schedule.
Indicates whether the labor work has been finished.
Flag marking pre‑assignment or estimate time before actual work; confirm with SME.
Planned end date of the labor activity.
Planned start date of the labor activity.
Date the labor was performed or recorded.
Code identifying the scheduling origin for this labor entry (e.g., manual, import).
User or system that created the schedule for this labor entry.
Code for the pay/bill rate category used for this labor (e.g., regular, overtime).
Reference source that defines rate categories used here (table/type indicator).
Classification of additional time added to this entry (e.g., travel, admin); confirm with SME.
Current or last recorded minutes on the active clock for this task.
Current or last recorded hours on the active clock for this task.
Decimal hours representation of the current or last clocked time.
Accumulated running clock duration used while actively clocked in (unit defined by system); confirm with SME.
Notes specific to time entry, separate from general labor comments.
Indicates whether extra time was added via an automated process rather than manual entry.
